  "result": "**Merge** preserves history as-is: it creates a new commit that ties two branch tips together, keeping both parent lineages intact. Non-destructive, but produces a branching graph.\n\n**Rebase** rewrites history: it replays your commits one-by-one on top of another branch, producing a linear sequence. Cleaner log, but the replayed commits have new SHAs — so rebasing already-pushed commits forces collaborators to reset.\n\nRule of thumb: merge for shared/public branches, rebase for local cleanup before pushing.",
